ot properly ordered in the dashboard.<\/li>\n<li>Fixed issue when invoicing project tasks and Select all tasks checkbox is checked.<\/li>\n<li>Fixed user can&#8217;t edit contracts if the customer is registered from customers area.<\/li>\n<li>Fixed shipping street was taken from billing street.<\/li>\n<li>Fixed error when uploading newsfeed attachment.<\/li>\n<li>Fixed invoice\/estimate\/expenses total not showing drop-down for years when no data exists in the new year.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3>Upgrading to version 1.9.8<\/h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Delete <strong>application\/libraries\/Elfinder_lib.php<\/strong> &#8211; No longer used (managed via Composer)<\/li>\n<li>Delete <strong>application\/libraries\/Encoding_lib.php<\/strong> &#8211; No longer used (managed via Composer)<\/li>\n<li>Delete <strong>application\/libraries\/Pusher.php<\/strong> &#8211; No longer used (managed via Composer)<\/li>\n<li>Delete<strong> application\/third_party\/Excel_reader <\/strong>folder &#8211; No longer used (managed via Composer)<\/li>\n<li>Delete <strong>application\/third_party\/elfinder <\/strong>folder &#8211; No longer used (managed via Composer)<\/li>\n<li>Delete <strong>application\/third_party\/slugify<\/strong> folder<strong> (if exists)<\/strong> &#8211; No longer used (managed via Composer)<\/li>\n<li>Delete <strong>application\/third_party\/omnipay<\/strong> folder &#8211; No longer used (managed via Composer), if you have any custom payment gateways that are using Omnipay from third_party folder, you should re-check them.<\/li>\n<li>Delete <strong>application\/third_party\/Encoding.php<\/strong> &#8211; No longer used (managed via Composer)<\/li>\n<li>Delete\u00a0<strong>application\/third_party\/tcpdf<\/strong>\u00a0 &#8211; No longer used (managed via Composer)<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<div>If you are using anywhere<strong> in your custom files<\/strong> the following code:<\/div>\n<div>\n<pre class=\"lang:default decode:true\">require_once APPPATH . 'third_party\/tcpdf\/tcpdf.php';<\/pre>\n<p>You must remove this line, <strong>otherwise just ignore this note.<\/strong><\/p>\n<h4>Custom Fields For Items<\/h4>\n<p><strong>In case you haven&#8217;t changed any files, you can just ignore this note.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>In version 1.9.8 there is custom fields for items feature added, in order to add this feature we needed to rewrite a lot of code including the PDF files and preview HTML files for invoices, estimates, proposals etc&#8230;.<\/p>\n<p>If you plan to use this feature and you are already using my_ prefixed files like my_invoicepdf.php\u00a0or my_invoicehtml.php<\/p>\n<p>Note that you should re-check all your my_ prefixed file where the items are used, here is a list of files you should re-check if they are my_ prefixed.<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>application\/views\/themes\/[theme]\/views\/invoicepdf.php<\/li>\n<li>application\/views\/themes\/[theme]\/views\/invoicehtml.php<\/li>\n<li>application\/views\/themes\/[theme]\/views\/estimatepdf.php<\/li>\n<li>application\/views\/themes\/[theme]\/views\/estimatehtml.php<\/li>\n<li>application\/views\/themes\/[theme]\/views\/proposalpdf.php<\/li>\n<li>application\/views\/themes\/[theme]\/views\/viewproposal.php<\/li>\n<li>application\/views\/themes\/[theme]\/views\/credit_note_pdf.php<\/li>\n<li>application\/views\/admin\/invoices\/invoice_preview_template.php<\/li>\n<li>application\/views\/admin\/invoices\/invoice.php<\/li>\n<li>application\/views\/admin\/estimates\/estimate_preview_template.php<\/li>\n<li>application\/views\/admin\/estimates\/_add_edit_items.php<\/li>\n<li>application\/views\/admin\/credit_notes\/credit_note.php<\/li>\n<li>application\/views\/admin\/credit_notes\/credit_note_preview_template.php<\/li>\n<li>application\/views\/admin\/proposals\/proposal.php<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>The <strong>[theme]<\/strong>\u00a0will be changed based on what theme for customers are you are using, in most cases be the default <strong>perfex<\/strong> theme (folder) or your <a href=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/customers-templates\/\">own theme<\/a> if you are using one for customers area.<\/p>\n<h4>All PHP dependencies\/libraries will be managed via Composer<\/h4>\n<p>In order to make Perfex CRM development easier and also use of third-party libraries more easier we needed to switch to Composer to manage our PHP dependencies, before Composer all the third party libraries were not well organized and were spread in different folders also they were hard to manage.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Added custom fields for items. Added Twilio SMS Support for limited actions. Added Stripe iDEAL payment gateway. Added Bitcoin support via Stripe. Added View and Delete permission for leads. Added option to add fixed amount discount (estimate\/invoice\/proposal\/credit_note) Added option to download all project files in a zip. Added Romanian language &#8211; Thanks to\u00a0http:\/\/www.hyper-creative.net\/ Added new [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[23],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-2683","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-changelog"],"aioseo_notices":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2683","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=2683"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2683\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=2683"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":